<br>
The following policy shall be enforced beginning February 6, 2002. Members on the roster as of that date will remain members.<br>
<br>
The minimum level that a main character must be to be invited to the guild is 20. <br>
<br>
Alts are welcome at any level, provided they meet the other admission requirements.<br>
<br>
Light Elves (high, wood, half) will be given preference, and recruitment shall be targetted to maintain at least 80% of main characters as elves.<br>
<br>
Light elves may be admitted without regard to class or diety choice.<br>
<br>
Dark-Elves and Non-elves may be admitted, providing they meet the following criteria:<br>
- they are neither necromancer nor shadowknight<br>
- they do not follow Cazic-Thule or Innoruk<br>
- they must learn to speak excellent Elvish<br>
- they must work on their faction so they can walk freely in Kelethin and Felwithe<br>
<br>
Prospective guild members should post their request to the admission forum.<br>
<br>
After being contacted by a recruiter, said recruiter should post in the private boards, the character's name, class, lvl, and any other information, thus allowing comments by other guild members.<br>
<br>
The officer's council will vote on all admissions.<br>
<br>
*amendments made 7/29/02:  Alts admitted at any level.  Minimum level requirement for new mains is 40*<br>
*re-amended 8/18/02: Minimum level requirement for new mains is 20*<br>
